# Local Paths

Per-machine paths and tool locations referenced from `CLAUDE.md` and other docs
in this repo. This file is gitignored — copy this `.example` to `local-paths.md`
and fill in your own values.

## Graphify

Used by §0 ("Understand the Codebase First") in `CLAUDE.md` to build the
codebase graph (`graphify-out/`) when one isn't already present.

- **CLI binary**: `~/bin/graphify` (the `graphify claude install` entry point;
  also commonly aliased to `graphify` on the shell `PATH`)
- **Python entry point**: `<graphify-checkout>/.venv/bin/python3`
  Used to drive the rebuild directly when the CLI hook is unavailable, e.g.:
  ```bash
  <graphify-checkout>/.venv/bin/python3 \
    -c "from graphify.watch import _rebuild_code; from pathlib import Path; _rebuild_code(Path('.'))"
  ```

## Reference runs of the post-PR review loop

`git-workflow.md` §"Capture follow-up tasks as new GitHub issues" mentions that
prior successful runs of the loop make good templates for issue shape. List
them here for your own projects, e.g.:

- `<owner>/<repo>` issues `#<from>`–`#<to>` — filed during the `<YYYY-MM-DD>`
  `known_issues` sweep.
